snippet: Some American officials said that the Russians want help analyzing forensic evidence from the charter plane that broke apart over the Sinai Peninsula, killing 224 people.

byline.original: By MICHAEL S. SCHMIDT and DAVID D. KIRKPATRICK
byline.contributor: Michael S. Schmidt reported from Washington, and David D. Kirkpatrick from Cairo. Neil MacFarquhar contributed reporting from Moscow, and Karin Roberts from New York.

lead_paragraph: Some American officials said that the Russians want help analyzing forensic evidence from the charter plane that broke apart over the Sinai Peninsula, killing 224 people.

headline.main: F.B.I. to Help Russia Investigate Plane Crash in Egypt
